SENATE BILL 898
J1 6lr3364
By: Senator McCray
Introduced and read first time: February 6, 2026
Assigned to: Finance
Committee Report: Favorable
Senate action: Adopted
Read second time: March 1, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Maryland Medical Assistance Program – Registered Behavior Technicians –
3 Reimbursement
4 FOR the purpose of requiring the Maryland Department of Health to provide
5 reimbursement for applied behavior analysis services provided by registered
6 behavior technicians under the Maryland Medical Assistance Program; prohibiting,
7 subject to a certain exception, the Department from requiring as a condition of
8 reimbursement that an individual receive a certain certification to provide applied
9 behavior analysis services as a registered behavior technician to Program recipients;
10 and generally relating to the Maryland Medical Assistance Program and applied
11 behavior analysis services.
12 BY adding to
13 Article – Health – General
14 Section 15–114.2
15 Annotated Code of Maryland
16 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
17 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
18 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
19 Article – Health – General
20 15–114.2.
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *sb0898*

2 SENATE BILL 898
1 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
2 INDICATED.
3 (2) (I) “APPLIED BEHAVIOR ANALYSIS” MEANS THE DESIGN,
4 IMPLEMENTATION, AND EVALUATION OF ENVIRONMENTAL MODIFICATIONS USING
5 BEHAVIORAL STIMULI AND CONSEQUENCES TO PRODUCE SOCIALLY SIGNIFICANT
6 IMPROVEMENTS IN HUMAN BEHAVIOR.
7 (II) “APPLIED BEHAVIOR ANALYSIS” INCLUDES THE DIRECT
8 OBSERVATIONS, MEASUREMENT, AND FUNCTIONAL ANALYSIS OF THE RELATIONS
9 BETWEEN ENVIRONMENT AND BEHAVIOR.
10 (3) “AUTISM SPECTRUM DISORDER” MEANS A GROUP OF
11 DEVELOPMENTAL DISORDERS:
12 (I) CHARACTERIZED BY PERSISTENT DEFICITS IN SOCIAL
13 COMMUNICATION AND SOCIAL INTERACTION ACROSS MULTIPLE CONTEXTS;
14 (II) CHARACTERIZED BY RESTRICTED, REPETITIVE PATTERNS
15 OF BEHAVIOR, INTERESTS, OR ACTIVITIES; AND
16 (III) WHOSE SYMPTOMS CAUSE CLINICALLY SIGNIFICANT
17 IMPAIRMENT IN SOCIAL, OCCUPATIONAL, OR OTHER IMPORTANT AREAS OF
18 CURRENT FUNCTIONING.
19 (4) “BOARD CERTIFIED BEHAVIOR ANALYST” MEANS A LICENSED
20 PROFESSIONAL WHO:
21 (I) RENDERS AND PROVIDES DIRECTION FOR APPLIED
22 BEHAVIOR ANALYSIS SERVICES THAT ARE PROVIDED TO INDIVIDUALS WITH AUTISM
23 SPECTRUM DISORDER; AND
24 (II) HAS OBTAINED A BOARD CERTIFIED BEHAVIOR ANALYST
25 CERTIFICATION.
26 (5) “BOARD CERTIFIED BEHAVIOR ANALYST–DOCTORAL” MEANS A
27 LICENSED PROFESSIONAL WHO:
28 (I) RENDERS AND PROVIDES DIRECTION FOR APPLIED
29 BEHAVIOR ANALYSIS TREATMENTS THAT ARE PROVIDED TO INDIVIDUALS WITH
30 AUTISM SPECTRUM DISORDER; AND

SENATE BILL 898 3
1 (II) HAS OBTAINED A BOARD CERTIFIED BEHAVIOR
2 ANALYST–DOCTORAL CERTIFICATION.
3 (6) “REGISTERED BEHAVIOR TECHNICIAN” MEANS A
4 PARAPROFESSIONAL WHO DELIVERS APPLIED BEHAVIOR ANALYSIS SERVICES THAT
5 ARE PROVIDED TO INDIVIDUALS WITH AUTISM SPECTRUM DISORDER UNDER THE
6 SUPERVISION OF:
7 (I) A LICENSED PSYCHOLOGIST;
8 (II) A BOARD CERTIFIED BEHAVIOR ANALYST–DOCTORAL; OR
9 (III) A BOARD CERTIFIED BEHAVIOR ANALYST.
10 (B) (1) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL PROVIDE REIMBURSEMENT FOR
11 APPLIED BEHAVIOR ANALYSIS SERVICES PROVIDED BY REGISTERED BEHAVIOR
12 TECHNICIANS TO PROGRAM RECIPIENTS WITH AUTISM SPECTRUM DISORDER.
13 (2) EXCEPT AS PROVIDED UNDER PARAGRAPH (3) OF THIS
14 SUBSECTION, THE DEPARTMENT MAY NOT REQUIRE AS A CONDITION OF
15 REIMBURSEMENT UNDER THE PROGRAM THAT AN INDIVIDUAL RECEIVE A
16 CERTIFICATION FROM THE BEHAVIOR ANALYST CERTIFICATION BOARD OR OTHER
17 CREDENTIALING ENTITY TO PROVIDE APPLIED BEHAVIOR ANALYSIS SERVICES AS A
18 REGISTERED BEHAVIOR TECHNICIAN.
19 (3) THE DEPARTMENT MAY REQUIRE AS A CONDITION OF
20 REIMBURSEMENT UNDER THE PROGRAM THAT AN INDIVIDUAL OBTAIN A CURRENT
21 CERTIFICATION ISSUED BY THE BEHAVIOR ANALYST CERTIFICATION BOARD OR
22 OTHER CREDENTIALING ENTITY TO PROVIDE APPLIED BEHAVIOR ANALYSIS
23 SERVICES AS A REGISTERED BEHAVIOR TECHNICIAN WITHIN 150 DAYS AFTER THE
24 INDIVIDUAL BEGINS PROVIDING APPLIED BEHAVIOR ANALYSIS SERVICES TO
25 PROGRAM RECIPIENTS AS A REGISTERED BEHAVIOR TECHNICIAN AND MAINTAIN
26 THE CERTIFICATION.
27 (C) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL ADOPT REGULATIONS NECESSARY TO CARRY
28 OUT THIS SECTION.
29 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall be construed to
30 apply only prospectively and may not be applied or interpreted to have any effect on or
31 application to any individual who provides applied behavior analysis services before the
32 effective date of this Act.
33 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
34 October 1, 2026.

4 SENATE BILL 898
